OL,3,CAssisted dying in Jersey: A step
OL,4,Ccloser to being legalised
OL,6,FHowever, if the person does not meet
OL,7,Fthe requirements for route 1, route 2
OL,8,Fwould allow for assisted dying if they
OL,9,Fhave an incurable physical condition
OL,10,Fthat is giving rise to "unbearable
OL,11,Fsuffering" that cannot be improved in
OL,12,Fa "tolerable" way.
OL,14,FThe distinction between route 1 and 2
OL,15,Fis that a individual does not have to
OL,16,Fhave a terminal illness in the latter,
OL,17,Falong with a life expectancy of six
OL,18,Fmonths, or twelve months in the case
OL,19,Fof neurodegenerative conditions.
