OL,3,CAssisted dying in Jersey: A step
OL,4,Ccloser to being legalised
OL,6,FInstead, it looks to other
OL,7,Fjurisdictions to make very broad
OL,8,Fcomparisons, and stresses that these
OL,9,Fshould be "regarded with caution".
OL,11,FFor example, in the state of Oregon in
OL,12,Fthe United States, 0.6% of deaths are
OL,13,Fassisted which would equate to 6 per
OL,14,Fyear in Jersey.
OL,16,FWhereas in Canada, 4.1% of deaths are
OL,17,Fassisted which would equate to 38
OL,18,Fannually on the island.
